   <talk_paragraph index="n2253_nophee-1" image="Trigger_AOD_Msoldier.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Nophee.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2253_nophee-1-a" mid="14" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$Norfe${sound:npc_Nophee_9827_qu_01.ogg}<BR>They are the <FONT color=#a82424>Child Guards</FONT> who were guarding the <FONT color=#a82424>confiscated items</FONT> at <FONT color=#086171>Abandoned Wharf</FONT>. Don’t worry. They don’t know who we are.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2253_nophee-1-a" image="QN_grugiru.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2253_nophee-1-b" mid="16" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>But what Gregory overheard at Abandoned Wharf worries me. He said the guards were there for a more important item and it could be a </FONT><FONT color=#a82424>special treasure</FONT><FONT color=#662500> like the relic.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2253_nophee-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Nophee.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2253_nophee-1-c" mid="18" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Norfe${sound:npc_Nophee_9827_qu_02.ogg}<BR>Hmm... That makes me think that maybe the <FONT color=#a82424>Empire is holding more inspections</FONT> because of that <FONT color=#a82424>item</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2253_nophee-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Nophee.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2253_nophee-2" mid="20" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Norfe$<BR>Why don’t you go and ask <FONT color=#086171>Vernicka</FONT> if he has any information while you’re there to give him the <FONT color=#086171>mana detector</FONT>? It catches signals well and I think it can be used now.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2253_nophee-2" image="QN_Vernicka.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Nophee.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2253_nophee-2-" mid="22" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$Norfe$<BR>I’ve already given him the manual on how to use the <FONT color=#086171>mana detector</FONT> so you just have to deliver the device to him. I’ll leave it to you then.<BR>
<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>* Take the mana detector to </FONT><FONT color=#086171>President Vernicka</FONT><FONT color=#7e12d2>.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2-a" mid="24" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka${sound:npc_Vernicka_9827_qu_01.ogg}<BR>Is that the <FONT color=#086171>mana detector</FONT> <FONT color=#086171>Norfe </FONT> told me about? I guess this can prevent the barrier from disappearing without a warning like what happened in Chiron Island. But that doesn’t mean we can let our guard down…….</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2-b" mid="26" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="25"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Thank you for working hard for Merca. We owe many debts to <FONT color=#086171>Lord Norfe</FONT> now.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2-c" mid="28" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="27"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Erm... Actually there’s something else I wanted to ask… </FONT><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Tell him what happened at Abandoned Wharf.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2-d" mid="30" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="29"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka${sound:npc_Vernicka_9827_qu_02.ogg}<BR><FONT color=#a82424>Red Lotus Palace’s Treasure House</FONT>…? The whole Mistland knows about it except you. That place is a treasure trove of the owner of Red Lotus Palace, <FONT color=#a82424>General Faran</FONT>. All the exquisite treasures of this world are stored there. It would be no surprise that another <FONT color=#a82424>special treasure</FONT> is added to that collection.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2-e" mid="32" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="31"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Well... That special treasure was delivered around the same time when security tightened in Red Lotus Palace.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2-f" mid="34" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="33"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka${sound:npc_Vernicka_9827_qu_03.ogg}<BR>It wouldn’t hurt to be cautious. I have already sent <FONT color=#a82424>spies</FONT> there but I’ve not heard from them for a long time. It would take me some time to get the latest news from them.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-3" mid="36" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="35"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Why don’t you get information from the merchants here? They travel across borders freely and must have gathered some useful information. In the meanwhile, I will try to find out whatever I can in other ways.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-3" image="QW_MercaPort.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-3-" mid="38" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="37"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka${sound:npc_Vernicka_9827_qu_04.ogg}<BR>First, collect information at <FONT color=#086171>Merca’s Port</FONT>. Merchants from all over the world gather there so there must be someone from <FONT color=#a82424>Red Lotus Palace</FONT> too. By the way, take this <FONT color=#a82424>mana detector</FONT> with you and pass it to <FONT color=#086171>Special Sentry Louis</FONT> on your way there.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
